metadata.name: Knights of Hiraeth #218
metadata.description:
The Knights of Hiraeth - Engulfed by the tempest's wrath and cast adrift in the unrelenting sea, a noble Knight succumbs to the ocean's bitter embrace. His life force ebbs away, surrendering him to the briny deep. He is eventually relinquished onto a distant shore, a foreign land that whispers tales of the unknown. His once formidable presence is reduced to mere driftwood, a silent feast for opportunistic crabs and relentless gulls, the tragedy of his demise echoed in their hungry cries.

However, his tale does not end there, for destiny had interwoven a different thread for this fallen Knight. A Druid, enigmatic and ageless, dwelt in the verdant shadows of the island's heart. Known to the elements but a stranger to time, the Druid was a sentinel of ancient lore and forgotten magic.

Moved by the Knight's tragic end, the Druid ventures forth from the forest's emerald shroud. He retrieves the lifeless remains and with an air of solemn determination, the Druid commences a ritual as old as the land itself.

Under the eerie full moonlight, the Druid chants in a language untouched by man, commanding the very essence of life and death. His words, a symphony of resurrection, vibrate through the silent night, echoing the Knight's call to the realm of the living.

And so, in the heart of Hiraeth, under the watchful eye of the mysterious Druid and the moon above, a warrior once lost to the tempest's fury embarks on his second chance at life, a testament to the enduring spirit of survival and the mysterious power of ancient magic.

metadata.name: Aracho
metadata.description: Throughout the ages murmurs have persisted about an enigmatic order of knights. These clandestine warriors, unbound by conventional rules and codes of conduct, carry out their missions with unyielding determination, guided by their own mysterious principles
